x4freetext: Experiment performed at the University
of Notre Dame Nuclear Science Laboratory using the
10-MV FN Tandem Van de Graaf.
Gamma rays were detected using NaI(Tl) array
HECTOR. The array consists of 16 NaI(Tl) crystals,
each with dimensions of 4"x 8"x 8". Scintillation light
from each crystal is read out by two photomultiplier
tubes. The crystals are assembled to form a 16" cube.
A 60 mm bore hole through the array allows for placing
the target in the center of the array. HECTOR array
allows for simultaneous measurement of the total
absorption spectrum and the individual gamma rays
contributing to the cascade.
